Entry 1<br>
<br>
<br>
The hour was late, and I sat upon my spider silk upholstered bench in front the vanity, wrapped my silken evening robe, and brushing my hair. The warm-toned lamplight illuminated my face, and I noticed the flame dancing in my pale blue eyes. I began to look intently at myself as I pulled the brush through my hair, examining my eyes, my skin, and every line and crease of my face. I set the platinum handled brush down upon the vanity table, and pulled my hair up and away from my neck with both hands. Holding it in place with my left hand, I used my right hand to slide a delicate ivory comb into the mass of hair to keep it in place. With the fingers of my right hand, I softly traced my cheekbones, and the line of my jaw. I ran my fingers along the edge of my pointed ear, and along the slope of my nose. With a sigh, I rested my hands in my lap, and began to stare at my features once again. A willful strand of my hair fell from the clip and brushed against my face and I reached up and pushed it behind my ear.<br>
<br>
I opened my right vanity drawer and took out the small jar of face crème that had been created especially for me by a talented alchemist in Shadow Haven. I smoothed a small amount over the entirety of my face, and placed the lid back in the jar. As I did, there seemed to be a knock followed by a bit of a thud against my chamber door, so I set the jar atop the vanity and went to see who was stirring outside my door so late at night.<br>
<br>
The heavy door opened with a cracking sound and then a creak. Leaning against the doorframe was a clearly inebriated Talastius, and in his hand was a small leather bound book. He attempted to greet me and bow, but in his impaired state, his greeting was nothing more than a rain of saliva accompanied by a bit of gibberish. His attempt at a bow caused him to fall into me. Chuckling a bit at him, I helped him to stand and led him to sit on the chest at the foot of my bed.<br>
<br>
After sitting him down, I studied him. His white hair was quite disheveled, and stained a pale burgundy in places. His eyes were narrow and unable to focus on me as he looked up. On his chin was a bit of drool, so I procured a handkerchief from my vanity and dabbed it off. It was then that I noticed his breath.<br>
<br>
Stepping back, I asked him why he had come.<br>
<br>
He lifted up the journal and held it out to me. I took it and began to flip through it, seeing that it was blank inside.<br>
<br>
“It’s for you, Mistress… a gift” he managed to slur out. “To write down your thoughts”.<br>
<br>
I was elated. It had been a great amount of time since I had received a gift, and this would get much use.<br>
<br>
I smiled widely at him and thanked him for the gift, then suggested he get some rest.<br>
<br>
With a nod, Talastius held out his arm for me to take and I helped him up from the chest. Once outside the door, Ugrak, a patrolling ogre guard approached, and asked if he could be of aid. I explained to him that Talastius needed to be taken to his quarters to rest, and that I was certainly naut strong enough to take him the full distance myself. He took Talastius from me, but before he took him away, I patted the knight on the cheek, chuckled at him, and wished him a good rest.<br>
